<!ENTITY sparc-common-desc '
  <para>The code production portion of the TDF compiler is under the control of
    a TDF translator, which translates a TDF capsule into an assembly source
    file. There are separate TDF translators for each target architecture. This
    manual page describes the translators which produce SPARC assembly code.
    There are two versions, one for SunOS, and one for Solaris</para>

  <para>It is recommended that <command>sparctrans</command> should not be
    invoked directly, but via the user interface &man.tendra.tcc;. The option
    <emphasis>-</emphasis><emphasis>opt</emphasis> can be passed to
    <command>sparctrans</command> by passing the option
    <option>-Wt,-</option><replaceable>opt</replaceable> to
    &man.tendra.tcc;.</para>
'>
